org.smpte.util

Class ListenerProcessor<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.smpte.util.ListenerProcessor<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class ListenerProcessor<T>
extends Object
implements Closeable
    The ListenerSupport class implements a performant, thread safe, listener subsystem that does not create temporary objects during the event dispatch process. The order in which listeners are registered determines the order by which the listeners are called during event dispatch. A listener may halt the delivery of events to subsequent listeners by throwing a StopDispatchException.
    Author:
    Steve Posick
